      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 84: This still can miss the early auth signal it is trying to protect against. The subscription is installed before addDevice(), but the predicate drops every event while operationId is 0; if addDeviceStateChanged is delivered on accountCallbackQueue before addDevice() returns and assigns operationId on this object, the PublishSubject event is discarded permanently. The serial daemon callback queue does not serialize access to this view-model property. Buffer account-matching auth events until operationId is known, or perform the operationId assignment and callback consumption on a single serialized path. For example:\n```suggestion\n// Subscribe before addDevice(), but do not discard account events while the op id is pending.\nvar pendingAuthResults \u003d [AuthResult]()\n\nself.accountService.authStateSubject\n    .filter { [weak self] authResult in\n        authResult.accountId \u003d\u003d self?.account.id\n    }\n    .observe(on: MainScheduler.instance)\n    .subscribe(onNext: { [weak self] authResult in\n        guard let self \u003d self else { return }\n        guard self.operationId !\u003d 0 else {\n            pendingAuthResults.append(authResult)\n            return\n        }\n        guard authResult.operationId \u003d\u003d self.operationId else { return }\n        // existing handling\n    })\n    .disposed(by: disposeBag)\n```",
