      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 236: The new ordering still depends on an assumption that is not enforced by this code: setupDeviceAuthObserver() ignores auth events while tempAccount is nil, but tempAccount is assigned later from an unstructured Task. Even if daemon callbacks are serialized internally, the Task continuation and this property assignment are not serialized with authStateSubject delivery, so an early auth event can still be dropped by the observer. Make the observer buffer account-auth events until tempAccount exists, or create the temporary account first and subscribe using a replaying/stateful stream that cannot lose already-emitted auth state.\n```suggestion\nsetupDeviceAuthObserver(bufferUntilAccountIsAvailable: true)\nTask {\n    let account \u003d try await accountsService.createTemporaryAccount()\n    await MainActor.run {\n        tempAccount \u003d account\n        processBufferedAuthEvents(for: account.id)\n    }\n}\n```",
